    <body>
        <p><MadCap:variable name="General.LBPro" /> only. If any <MadCap:variable name="General.changeset" /> in a deployment fails, <code>--rollback-on-error</code> stops the <code>update</code> operation and  rolls back all <MadCap:variable name="General.changeset" />s you just deployed. Available in <MadCap:variable name="General.Liquibase" /> 4.18.0+. <b>Default: <code>false</code></b>. </p>
        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;Note: &lt;/b&gt;">A <MadCap:variable name="General.changeset" /> marked <code>failOnError=false</code> does not trigger as an error, so <code>rollback-on-error</code> will not occur. Additionally, if a <MadCap:variable name="General.changeset" /> is not auto-rollback compliant or does not have a rollback script, then <code>rollback-on-error</code> does not occur for any <MadCap:variable name="General.changeset" />. Read more: <code><MadCap:xref href="../../../../../concepts/changelogs/attributes/fail-on-error.htm">failOnError</MadCap:xref></code>.</p>
    </body>
</html>